  "text": "The Android Activity lifecycle is implemented across four key files in the aosp-mirror/platform_frameworks_base repository:\n\n1. **Activity.java** (core/java/android/app/Activity.java) - Defines the public class Activity which extends ContextThemeWrapper. This is the base class that application activities inherit from and contains the lifecycle callback methods including onCreate(), onStart(), onResume(), onPause(), onStop(), and onDestroy().\n\n2. **ActivityThread.java** (core/java/android/app/ActivityThread.java) - Implements the public final class ActivityThread which extends ClientTransactionHandler. This class represents the main thread of an Android application and is responsible for driving lifecycle transitions by processing ActivityLifecycleItem messages from the ActivityTaskManagerService.\n\n3. **ActivityRecord.java** (services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityRecord.java) - Implements the final class ActivityRecord which extends WindowToken and implements WindowManagerService.AppFreezeListener. This is the server-side representation of an activity in the ActivityTaskManagerService, tracking activity state, configuration, and lifecycle information.\n\n4. **ActivityTaskManagerService.java** (services/core/java/com/android/server/wm/ActivityTaskManagerService.java) - Implements the public class ActivityTaskManagerService which extends IActivityTaskManager.Stub. This is the system service that manages activity stacks, tasks, and coordinates lifecycle transitions by sending transaction items to the client-side ActivityThread."
}

